Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees. Drain and rinse the @artichokes{1%jar}. Halve the @mixed olives{1%oz}, artichokes, and @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Mince the @garlic{2%clove}. Thinly slice the @baby gem lettuce{1}. Tear the @fresh mozzarella{4%oz} into small pieces.

Place each @flatbreads{2} onto a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Top with the mozzarella, olives, artichokes, tomatoes, and @feta cheese{1/4%cup}. Top with as much onion and garlic as you like. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in the oven for ~{7-10%minutes}, until the crust is crisp and the cheese is melted.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{} toss the lettuce with a drizzle of @balsamic vinegar{2%tablespoon} and @olive oil{2%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Finish: Top the flatbread with the salad, cut into slices, and enjoy!